## Why This Is Asked

Tests ability to design and reason about multi-cycle 3-valued constraint propagation, a common motif in policy engines and configuration management where Unknowns must be carefully propagated to avoid false constraints.

## Key Concepts

- Kleene 3-valued logic: T>U>F ordering, ¬T=F, ¬F=T, ¬U=U; ∨/∧ as max/min.
- Implication as a→b = ¬a ∨ b.
- Temporal constraints: handling two cycles and cross-time implications.
- Backtracking propagation: prune values that would force a constraint to F.

## Code Example

```javascript
// Kleene three-valued helpers
const order = {F:0, U:1, T:2};
function not(x){ return x==='T'?'F': x==='F'?'T':'U'; }
function litOr(a,b){ return order[a] >= order[b] ? a : b; }
function litAnd(a,b){ return order[a] <= order[b] ? a : b; }
function implies(a,b){ // ¬a ∨ b
  const na = not(a);
  return litOr(na, b);
}
```

